like my little healer.  The problem is that we have so many useless spells. <br>
<br>
List of useless spell lines.<br>
<br>
Yallp<br>
If this isnt a obvious joke then I don't know what is.  Its ok until about lvl 24 then you rarely use it again.  This line should be replaced by something else.  Like a prayer type spell that would work like bard songs in a way.  They can be interupted to increaces armor class or resists a bit.  Make the recovery of the prayer long like divine aura so as to not unbalance the usefulness of bards or make them too powerful.<br>
<br>
Pacify, Atone, ect....<br>
Yes, I have used them effectively a few times.  But lets get real.  When are you NOT in agro range?  Only good in those very rare solo situations where you can root and run.  By then you dont have enough mana to cast it anyway.<br>
(note: could be made useful if mana cost was drasticly reduced)<br>
<br>
AoE damage spell<br>
Not really useless, just too expensive to cast.  Considering the only reason to do this is to draw alot of attention off your group then DA and run.<br>
<br>
Summon Hammer Spell<br>
Again not completely useless.  Saved my arse many times.  Problem is you have to hold it.  The idea of being able to summon a hammer comes from AD&amp;D with the shillelagh.  A mystical club that the cleric could summon to defend them in a fight.  This weapon was not carried by the cleric, but controled by the cleric much like enchanter pets are in the game.  This little feature would make this line much more useful. <br>
<br>
Additionally, cleric should be able to bind wound to 90% of health.  Mabey a spell that enchants the bandages to be able to do this.<br>
<br>
<br>
Any additional thoughts?  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Tagarth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r Where's the corpse.</span><br>  Posts: 1257<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/17/01 12:15:19 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/HeadShots/HethralHead2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Should clerics spells be changed</span><hr size=1> yaulp: these are just fun spells, besides occasionally being able to out-tank a pally a couple levels lower than you is fun.<br>
<br>
pacify line: crap. atone: pinacle of wonderfulness, it's a memblur, use it to reduce your agro in epic fights or root and atone something that's annoying you while you're traveling.<br>
<br>
AoE damage: use only when in company of wizzards/enchanters they'll get off two to your one and it finishes just in time for you to need to group heal :)<br>
<br>
Summon Hammer: don't be totaly naked when you get killed a second time, and you won't eat it by accident. 'nuff said.<br>
<br>
<br>
Personally I find uses for most of these, even if it's just for mucking around and having fun (yaulp)<br>
