<br>
I think the blind spells and the lull series with the exception of atone are the only cleric spells I've never cast.<br>
<br>
Cure blindness actually comes in handy in Dragon Necropolis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gruid</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.thaaron.com/moogle/images/icons/Mog_w.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disturbed Little Boy</span><br>  Posts: 1349<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/19/01 10:16:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   My thoughts...</span><hr size=1> I think that yaulp was put in just so it would cross over to the paladin spells... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uorri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fire Brand</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/28/01 5:21:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Should clerics spells be changed</span><hr size=1> I like hethral's replies, also...<br>
<br>
sometimes a cleric can attract tons of aggro with aoe, with the intent to da. I've done this alot and it comes out great, really. You have done 200 to 600 pts damage to surrounding mobs, then da, and failed mezzes wont immediately draw aggro. <br>
<br>
Plus, when it comes down to it, there are 2 characters in a 6 person group who seem to always die first; the healer and the crowd control. If it looks real bad, cast aoe so the evac person can cast. You would be left behind by having da on anyway.<br>
<br>
and ya, the summoned hammer so your naked corpse can be rezzed. really really important. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 855<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/29/01 1:35:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://216.242.60.166/chicktourney_com/larges/415.jpg width=110 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Should clerics spells be changed</span><hr size=1> At level 9, when you can summon a 6/32 1h blunt that is magical, clerics can kick some serious ass vs wisps, especially considering that combine weapons cost about 60P.  (not everyone twinks, or can twink on a new server).  Even a 6/29 weapon isn't bad at level 24.<br>
<br>
Atone rules.  You think mem blur sucks?  What, are you on crack?<br>
<br>
The pacify line of spells would be ok if it was much less resisted.  You can use it from time to time, but currently it resists too much.  One use I've had out of it with my paladin was to use lull or whatever upgrade I had to lower the aggro radius of a mob so I could run past it without aggroing. <p>=============================
